    {
      "id": "013c8155ce8372bfc68b1f74",
      "title": "My old Windows software",
      "summary": "After moving to Windows PC from Atari ST I discovered Visual Basic and my mind was blown by the possibilities of laying out a graphical user interface using the mouse and adding code to make it do stuff. I jumped in and made a whole bunch of Windows software, including some world-first features like hot-corners to invoke the screen saver and being able to q…",
      "image": "https://cdn.gingerbeardman.com/images/posts/tektonix-software.png",
